The paper discusses techniques to improve the retrieval effectiveness of a search engine, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). The use of a sequence-to-sequence model and relevant datasets suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), while the mention of re-ranking components suggests a focus on deep learning (DL) and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
